Privacy Policy for ECG+
Effective Date:
1 Jan 2025
Heartworks Pty Ltd ("we", "our", "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how ECG+ ("the App") collects, uses, and safeguards your data when you use our services.
1. Information We Collect
Health Data
ECG+ accesses ECG data and heart-related health information from Apple HealthKit and Apple Watch to provide analysis and insights. This data includes, but is not limited to:
ECG recordings
Heart rate
Heart rate variability (HRV)
Metadata associated with ECG sessions (e.g., time, date)
Note:
We do
not
collect or store your HealthKit data on our servers. All health data remains on your device unless you choose to share it.
App Usage Data
We may collect anonymous usage data to improve app performance and user experience. This includes:
App interactions (e.g., features used)
Crash reports
Device information (e.g., model, iOS version)
This data is
aggregated
and
not linked
to your identity or health information.
2. How We Use Your Data
To provide ECG analysis and display results within the app.
To enhance app features and functionality.
To troubleshoot technical issues and improve stability.
To comply with legal and regulatory obligations if required.
We do
not
sell, rent, or share your personal or health data with third parties for marketing purposes.
3. Data Security
We prioritize the security of your data. ECG+ uses Apple's secure HealthKit framework, and all data remains encrypted and stored locally on your device. App usage data, when collected, is anonymized and securely transmitted.
4. Your Rights and Choices
You control access to your health data via Apple Health settings.
You can revoke ECG+ access to HealthKit at any time.
You may delete the app and its associated data from your device at your discretion.
5. Third-Party Services
ECG+ does not integrate with third-party services that access your personal or health data. All analysis is performed locally on your device.
6. Children's Privacy
ECG+ is not intended for use by children under 13. We do not knowingly collect data from children without verifiable parental consent.
7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in technology, laws, or our services. Updates will be posted in the app and/or on our website, and the effective date will be revised accordingly.
8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about your privacy, please contact us at:
Heartworks Pty Ltd
Email: hello@heartworks.com.au
Website: www.heartworks.com.au